To integrate **role-based API access**, **agent scraping functions**, and **secure invocation with enforcement** into your existing **Godmode Agentic Orchestrator**, here's a **fail-proof modular extension** that aligns with your current infrastructure (Firebase + Cloud Functions + agent execution logic) and content from your docs【9†Voice Control Optimization Guide】【11†Platform Strategy & UX】.

---

## ✅ MODULE OVERVIEW

### 🔐 1. Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

#### Roles:
```ts
type Role = 'admin' | 'scraper' | 'viewer';
```

#### Permissions Map:
```ts
const rolePermissions: Record<Role, string[]> = {
  admin: ['*'],
  scraper: ['notebookScraperAgent', 'urlScraperAgent'],
  viewer: ['viewScanLogs']
};
```

#### In `auth/roles.ts`:
```ts
const userStore = new Map<string, { roles: Role[] }>([
  ['adminUser', { roles: ['admin'] }],
  ['scraperUser', { roles: ['scraper'] }],
  ['viewerUser', { roles: ['viewer'] }],
]);

export function getUserRoles(userId: string): Role[] {
  return userStore.get(userId)?.roles || [];
}

export function userHasPermission(userId: string, agentName: string): boolean {
  const roles = getUserRoles(userId);
  return roles.some(role => rolePermissions[role]?.includes(agentName) || rolePermissions[role]?.includes('*'));
}
```

---

### 🤖 2. Scraping Agents (Agent Functions)

#### `agents/notebookScraperAgent.ts`
```ts
import axios from 'axios';

export const notebookScraperAgent = {
  name: 'notebookScraperAgent',
  run: async (_action: string, userId: string, context: any) => {
    const url = context?.pageUrl;
    const res = await axios.get(url);
    return {
      status: 'success',
      snippet: res.data.substring(0, 200),
    };
  },
  onFail: async (_action: string, _userId: string, err: any) => ({
    status: 'fail',
    message: err.message
  })
};
```

#### `agents/urlScraperAgent.ts`
```ts
const allowedDomains = ['your.notebook.lm', 'example.com'];

export const urlScraperAgent = {
  name: 'urlScraperAgent',
  run: async (_action: string, userId: string, context: any) => {
    const url = context?.url;
    const domain = new URL(url).hostname;
    if (!allowedDomains.includes(domain)) throw new Error(`Domain not allowed: ${domain}`);
    const res = await axios.get(url);
    return { status: 'success', contentLength: res.data.length };
  },
  onFail: async (_action: string, _userId: string, err: any) => ({
    status: 'fail',
    message: err.message
  })
};
```

---

### 🔁 3. Secure Agent Execution Layer

#### `agents/safeExecuteAgent.ts`
```ts
import { userHasPermission } from '../auth/roles';

export async function safeExecuteAgent(agent: Agent, action: string, userId: string, context?: any) {
  if (!userHasPermission(userId, agent.name)) {
    return { error: `User ${userId} lacks permission for ${agent.name}` };
  }
  try {
    return await agent.run(action, userId, context);
  } catch (err) {
    return agent.onFail(action, userId, err);
  }
}
```

---

### ☁️ 4. Cloud Function Endpoint (Firebase-ready)

#### `functions/agentRouter.ts`
```ts
import * as functions from 'firebase-functions';
import { agents } from './agents/registry';
import { safeExecuteAgent } from './agents/safeExecuteAgent';

export const executeAgent = functions.https.onRequest(async (req, res) => {
  const { agentName, action, userId, context } = req.body;
  const agent = agents[agentName];
  if (!agent) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Agent not found' });

  const result = await safeExecuteAgent(agent, action, userId, context);
  return res.json(result);
});
```

